The guideline of this medical procedure in Korea was enacted in 2000, and the candidates to outpatient cesarean delivery are women with two or more middle back to back or lower back to back delivery with two or more children and women with twins, breech, and cephalon being the second. We reviewed 6352 outpatient cesarean section which was performed between April 1, 2003 to March 31, 2006 in Hanyang University Hospital. We analyzed the indications, maternal, fetal, and neonatal outcomes. The most common indications for outpatient cesarean section (40.4%) were middle back to back or lower back to back delivery after two or more children with the mean age of 32.8 years.
